        "title": "fix(security): block build tool env overrides",
        "body": "## Summary\n\nHardens host exec environment sanitization for GHSA-xvhv-h97q-px99 by blocking additional build-tool executable substitution environment variables.\n\n## Changes\n\n- Add missing Rust/Cargo, make, and Mercurial executable/tool selection variables to the shared host env security policy.\n- Add narrow Cargo target runner/linker override detection for `CARGO_TARGET_*_{RUNNER,LINKER}` without blocking non-executable settings such as `CARGO_TARGET_DIR`.\n- Regenerate the macOS host env security policy mirror and extend sanitizer/baseline regression coverage.\n\n## Validation\n\n- `node scripts/run-vitest.mjs src/infra/host-env-security.test.ts src/infra/host-env-security.policy-parity.test.ts src/infra/host-env-security.reported-baseline.test.ts`\n- `git diff --check`\n- `.agents/skills/autoreview/scripts/autoreview --mode local` (clean)\n\n## Notes\n\nAI-assisted change. `USER.md` was updated locally for the requested security fixer worklog and intentionally left out of this commit.\n\nReal behavior proof:\nBehavior addressed: request-scoped host exec env overrides for build-tool executable substitution are rejected consistently.\nReal environment tested: local OpenClaw checkout on branch `736`.\nExact steps or command run after this patch: `node scripts/run-vitest.mjs src/infra/host-env-security.test.ts src/infra/host-env-security.policy-parity.test.ts src/infra/host-env-security.reported-baseline.test.ts`.\nEvidence after fix: targeted sanitizer tests pass, including rejection of the newly covered keys and preservation of `CARGO_TARGET_DIR`.\nObserved result after fix: 3 test files passed, 42 tests passed.\nWhat was not tested: full CI and live end-to-end exec flows were not run locally.\n",
